CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 27, 1954, pg. 21 reads: "Herron Hill P-TA Rallies to Keep Teen Canteen - Crafts - Frank Walchak is the instructor here unveiling a new project which will occupy these youngsters most of the evening."
TitMainTitle: Teacher Frank Walchak supervising group of boys, and girls, including girl standing on right wearing plaid shirt, working on arts and crafts projects in classroom in Herron Hill Junior High School
